NAME

    ExtUtils::FindFunctions - Find functions in external libraries


DESCRIPTION

    This module provides the "have_functions()" function which can be used
    to check if given functions are provided by an external library. Its aim
    is to be used as an embedded library by Makefile.PL which needs such
    facilities. Use the install-extutils-findfunctions command to embed it
    in your distribution.


INSTALLATION

    To install this module, run the following commands:

        perl Makefile.PL
        make
        make test
        make install


    Alternatively, to install with Module::Build, you can use the 
    following commands:

        perl Build.PL
        ./Build
        ./Build test
        ./Build install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

    After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the 
    perldoc command.

        perldoc ExtUtils::FindFunctions

    You can also look for information at:

        Search CPAN
            http://search.cpan.org/dist/ExtUtils-FindFunctions

        CPAN Request Tracker:
            http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=ExtUtils-FindFunctions

        AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
            http://annocpan.org/dist/ExtUtils-FindFunctions

        CPAN Ratings:
            http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/ExtUtils-FindFunctions

